         Personally all of you have a point, and the idea that wizards have gotten way too much mana regen is certainly valid, though I believe it boils down MORE to mod rods than merely mana regen - mod rods combined with shamans can virtually give any class unlimited mana, which nullifies one of our greatest advantages (having virtually unlimited mana).  Yet even so, I stand by my belief that necros are quite balanced facing mobs that resist squat, but not very balanced when considered in the greater scheme of things because we lose way too much of our abilities if a mob resists just one of our key resistances.  Drop FP & Pyro and you lose half of your DPS.  Drop magic and you can't heal yourself efficiently.  Drop disease and no group taps.  Wizards don't suffer this problem and neither do healers.  Mages are too busy making mod rods to care about their nukes.  And melees just do crap damage against Luclin mobs overall.  In other words, wizards have a huge adavantage here because they can hit anything and everything with similar efficiency - something no other class can claim.</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
