         <b>You (wizards) do the most damage in the shortest amount of time.</P><P>Necros do the most damage in a long period of time, or the most damage per bar of mana.</b></P><P>And if you crunch the numbers and totally throw out resists/aggro/summoning/modrods/flowing thought/KEI, Verant is still correct.</P><P>Look at it like Verant does:</P><P>Funeral Pyre = 2160 HP for 450 mana = 4.8 dmg/mana<BR>Garrison's = 2100 HP for 540 mana = 3.9 dmg/mana</P><P>Which gives us the clearly superior edge in dmg/mana ratio. Right? Now granted in the world of the modrod2, KEI, FT gear and bards, wizards can run on unlimited mana (as can we) and they can continually cast 7 Garrisons for every one of our Funeral Pyres (again, in an aggro free, perfect world), but Funeral Pyre is more efficient. Now if you roll up on a 32k mob and assume DoT stacking, 3 necros could drop said mob in 5 minutes (FP * 3 * 5 casts) = 32k for 6750 mana total, while it would take 16 casts of Garrisons at a mana cost of 8640 and it would take 48 seconds. So the necromancer is 28% more efficient in dmg/mana. But only in a perfect world where a mob will give you the 5 minutes of aggro free fun to burn it down with Funeral Pyre.</P><P>Verant loves to do these theoretical, perfect world, no-aggro, no summon, no AE, no mob-HP-regen comparisons to show you that their claim is absolutely correct. Also add in the uber dmg of 70 per hit from EoT pet, since they never miss and always hit for max on every mob, and necros do amazing damage. Simply amazing. LOL. /sarcasm off</P><P>But what is the answer to ManaBurn? Where is the unresistable DoT equivalent of the 17k dmg per 3500 mana that is 28% better? Where is the uber DoT that does 21,760 dmg (since DoTs don't crit) in 42/48/54 seconds for my bar of mana? And if it was in the game, would we be able to grind AAXP to get it, or would it require a quest involving a shard from Vulak, Emp, Seru and Aten? With no crit on LifeBurn, where is our DoT efficiency superiority and even with crits, would we be doing 17k bombs with LB?</P><P>What about the Bane series? Where is the DoT that is 28% better than Porlos/Hsagra and unresistable to dragons and giants? I bet alot of 60 necros would happily do a quest if they thought they could get a 2560 dot for 450 mana that was totally unresistable by dragons/giants. I know I would.</P><P>We can do plenty more than nuke, to be sure. But where is the unresistable, raid helping ability? If they fix Lifeburn and let it crit, maybe that's the answer. Amp up the DoTs in the post stack world and that is good too. But old excuses no longer work in the brave new Luclin world.</P><P><b>Venjenz</b></P><P>"...the darkest magic...my soul swims in it."</P><P>Edited by - Venjenz on 08/27/2002  12:33:23<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
