        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="63617"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/27/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 15:19:03</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=7942"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=7942')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=63617&amp;TOPIC_ID=7564&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=DPS+and+the+myth+that+necros+are+not+good+at+it&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         See guys, the problem here is really this.  A necro whips out his Best DoT for the encounter, then Uses it as soon as he can.  What does he do then?  He has to get out his SECOND best dot for the encounter, and use it too.  Then he has to whip out his 3rd best DoT for the encounter and use it.  All up until the best dot wears off. This kind of Reminds me of Bards Twisting their Songs, casting another song before the 1st one wears off.</P><P>What does a Wizard do?  He uses his best nuke for the encounter.  What does he do next?  He uses the SAME DAMN SPELL again.  Because he doesn't have to dig out a different DD, cause can already use it again.</P><P>When Verant put in DoT stacking, they got rid of Half of the Necro's problem with Dmg on Ubermob Raids, which was the "1 necro is the same dmg output as 30 Necros" problem.  They solved that one, but at the same time made it abundantly clear that we couldn't stack our own same dot more than once.  Why Not? How is that overpowering?  Sure we're not supposed to do insane DD dmg, I understand, but If We can stack our own DoT's we STILL won't be able to do insane dmg, hell it wouldn't even be Wizzy Dmg.  And it would still take more time to kill the mob in the first place.</P><P>Picture Chain Casting Funeral Pyre on a mob, every chance you got, since the duration is 9 ticks or 54 seconds, we can only stack 9 FP's max on a mob at any point and time, since they would be wearing off every tick after 9.  Now that's the same 2k dmg per FP, as 2k dmg that wizzys get to do every 8 seconds. For as long as mana holds out anyway.  The resulting dps would be like the following.</P><P>Tick 0, 0 dmg, 1st DoT takes hold<BR>Tick 1, 240 dmg, 2nd Dot takes hold<BR>Tick 2, 480 dmg, 3rd DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 3, 720 dmg, 4th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 4, 960 dmg, 5th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 5, 1200 dmg, 6th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 6, 1440 dmg, 7th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 7, 1680 dmg, 8th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 8, 1920 dmg, 9th DoT takes Hold<BR>Tick 9, 2160 dmg, 10th DoT takes Hold, 1st DoT wears off<BR>Tick 10, 2160 dmg, 11th DoT takes Hold, 2nd DoT wears off<BR>Tick 11, 2160 dmg, 12th DoT takes Hold, 3rd DoT wears off<BR>...<BR>Add infinitum</P><P>This allows a Necro to gradually build up their dps, from 0dps to Max dps in 9 ticks, using Funeral pyre.</P><P>Now lets look at wizzy dmg using their best nuke, Garrisons, as I used our best DoT Funeral Pyre.</P><P>Tick 0, 0 dmg, Garrisons still being casted through tick<BR>Tick 1, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 2, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 3, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 4, 0 dmg, Garrions still being cast through tick<BR>Tick 5, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 6, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 7, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 8, 0 dmg, Garrions still being cast through tick<BR>Tick 9, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 10, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>Tick 11, 2100 dmg, if not resisted and not critted<BR>...<BR>Add infinitum</P><P>Necro Dps vs Wizzy dps per tick<BR>Tick 0 : Necro dps = 0 : Wizzy dps = 0<BR>Tick 1 : Necro dps = 20 : Wizzy dps = 175<BR>Tick 2 : Necro dps = 40 : Wizzy dps = 233<BR>Tick 3 : Necro dps = 60 : Wizzy dps = 263<BR>Tick 4 : Necro dps = 80 : Wizzy dps = 210<BR>Tick 5 : Necro dps = 100 : Wizzy dps = 233<BR>Tick 6 : Necro dps = 120 : Wizzy dps = 250<BR>Tick 7 : Necro dps = 140 : Wizzy dps = 262<BR>Tick 8 : Necro dps = 160 : Wizzy dps = 233<BR>Tick 9 : Necro dps = 180 : Wizzy dps = 245<BR>Tick 10 : Necro dps = 180 : Wizzy dps = 254<BR>Tick 11 : Necro dps = 180 : Wizzy dps = 262</P><P>The wizzy still has higher dps over the Necro, but the necro still has his dps capped, he can't do any more dmg. How would this be overpowering? We still use mana.  Self Stacking our DoT's along with DoT crits would finally put the Necro class back where it should have been since Kunark Came out.</P><P>The funniest part is, It's even the way they wanted us to be, lower dps on low hp mobs, and High Dps on higher hp mobs.  Honestly, this is what we've been lacking.</P><P>Reepr<BR>Warlock of Lanys<BR><Sigil><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

